replies.body:
Depends what you enjoy more =D they play very differently

Zed really feels like a shadow assassin, a lot of trickery and re positioning to be had with W and R (you can even use R to dodge key abilities). Hes all about coming in silent and swift, bursting someone and disappearing into the shadows. {{champion:238}} 

Yasuo is more about flowing in and out of combat, putting out consistently high damage and using windwall and ult at opportune moments. Hes more about dueling and weaving in and out while dishing out damage (Q) and charging his shield. {{champion:157}} 

I vote for {{champion:238}} though, but thats because his gameplay fits my play style more and I love tricking people with shadow swapping.
